# voit/doctor

A whole-repo health pass that brings everything VOIT-related to its latest coherent
state, so the NEXT session starts oriented. Where `voit/dogfood` turns VOIT on the
plugin (promise/behavior drift, graduating conventions into shipped code), doctor
tends THIS project: it regenerates the project overview, folds accumulated learnings
back into voit-memory, and proves the base is healthy. No slice, no ceremony.

Doctor writes to voit-memory and the handoff (per-project, gitignored); dogfood writes
to the plugin (the commit is its record). They compose - doctor surveys and may
recommend `/dogfood`; dogfood graduates conventions doctor then reflects in the
overview. Doctor does NOT fix plugin drift itself; it names it and defers.

## the loop

1. SURVEY the whole repo and live state - build the current picture before writing:
   - git: branch, `git status`, recent commits, `git worktree list`, `git branch`.
   - bus: `python3 .voit/scripts/bus.py roster` (who is live), inbox for unread.
   - voit-memory: the decisions, the slice plans (`.voit/memory/voit/*` and `.../impl/*`).
   - plugin surface: commands, agents, hooks, jd procedures - what exists now.
2. OVERVIEW - (re)generate `.voit/memory/overview.jd` from reality, REPLACING the old one
   (regenerate, never append): what the project is, its architecture and key
   components, current state, slices done vs in-flight, the load-bearing decisions
   and conventions, and the entry points. This is the single document a fresh session
   reads to get oriented; keep it current and tight.
3. FOLD IN learnings - consolidate voit-memory so it stays coherent, not a pile:
   capture any decision since the last pass, merge overlapping entries, prune impl
   notes for slices already merged to `main`, correct stale "known nits", mark
   superseded entries. Durable knowledge in, cruft out.
4. SYNC the base - if `.voit/` is a synced copy of a cache-installed plugin (not this
   repo's vendored source), refresh the plugin first: `claude plugin update voit@voit` (best-effort;
   offline is fine, vendored setups skip this). `jd build --recursive` rebuilds the
   graph store so the manual
   resolves; confirm hooks are executable. Re-run `bash .voit/scripts/setup.sh`
   (idempotent) so voit-memory, `.gitignore`, and the `.claude/settings.json` wiring
   (default `agent: voit:vision` + the `statusLine`) are all present, and the `jd` binary
   is installed if missing - it only fills missing keys, never clobbers a user's own.
   Then `bash .voit/scripts/test.sh` MUST
   be green. If a plugin promise/behavior mismatch surfaces, name it and recommend
   `/dogfood` - do not fix it here.
5. HANDOFF - if a tracked `handoff.md` exists, refresh it to match the current
   structure and point at voit-memory / `.voit/memory/overview.jd` as canonical. Keep it an
   at-a-glance pointer, not a second source of truth.
6. REPORT - what changed, the current state in one paragraph, and what the next
   session should pick up first.

Precise and current: the overview mirrors reality, voit-memory holds only what still
matters, the base is green. Run doctor at the end of a working session or the start
of a fresh one.
